got production error after upgrade React-Intl, Could not find required intl object. needs to exist in the component ancestry

I know, some other questions already on this, but none of them discuss about production env, only testing component, my question is about production environment. So, after upgrade react-intl i got this error: Uncaught Error: [React Intl] Could not find required `intl` object. needs to exist in the component ancestry. idk why, i try find solution about this, even on formatjs github issue still not fix this error but if i don't upgrade this, react-int old version doesn't support with nodejs 16 or latest react@17.x , i need this latest react btw to support other packages too. So my specs: Node version: 16.14 (LTS) NPM Version: 8.3.x Packages: react: 17.x @mui/core: 5.x <<< i need this with latest react because for minimum requirements (1 more line was trimmed) i already set IntlProvider App.js
...
EDIT : so react-intl won't load if your components got errors, because it's wrapper component. The solution is simple, fix your errors on your components then react-intl will be execute properly
